
Overview of noun disaster

The noun disaster has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (7) catastrophe, disaster -- (a state of extreme (usually irremediable) ruin and misfortune; "lack of funds has resulted in a catastrophe for our school system"; "his policies were a disaster")
2. (7) calamity, catastrophe, disaster, tragedy, cataclysm -- (an event resulting in great loss and misfortune; "the whole city was affected by the irremediable calamity"; "the earthquake was a disaster")
3. (1) disaster -- (an act that has disastrous consequences)
